Agreed!  I literally just dealt with this eariler in the work week, spent hours trying to figure out why an error wasn&#x27;t properly being thrown in my unit tests ... forgot to catch the promise chain -.-<p>This applies to functions that are async as well in babel:<p><pre><code>    async function get(url) {
        throw new Error(&#x27;hi there&#x27;);
    }

    // wont throw the error
    get(&#x27;http://google.com&#x27;);

    // catch the error
    get(&#x27;http://google.com&#x27;).catch(function(err) {
        throw err;
    });</code></pre>
